{
  "question_id": "4d092040-7e90-429b-86e2-42ae7f3e22ff",
  "short_text": "Inverted Right Angled Triangle - 4",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print an **Inverted Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using numbers.\r\n\r\n```\r\n4444\r\n 333\r\n  22\r\n   1\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing numbers as an **Inverted Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 3`,\r\n\r\n- Print the numbers on **3** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-inverted-right-angled-triangle-4.png\r\n' widthPercent='50'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates one space (\" \").\r\n- The Number in the box indicates a number (\"3 \").\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n```\r\n333\r\n 22\r\n  1\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "b7a90d18-7fcb-4ddb-a442-285786821a07",
      "code_content": "rows = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, rows + 1):\n\n    number = (rows + 1) - each_number\n    \n    spaces = \" \" * (each_number - 1)\n    numbers = str(number) * number\n    print(spaces + numbers)\n",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
